## Portfolio design & video stack (Cursor skills)

Use the matching **Cursor Agent Skill** (`SKILL.md`) for depth; this rule is the **routing layer** when working under **design / brand / illustration / video** personas.

| Tool | Skill name | Role |
|------|------------|------|
| **Anthropic Claude Design** | `claude-design` | Hosted design + brand systems + exports; Claude subscription / Team workflows; handoff to Claude Code when applicable. |
| **Open Design** (nexu-io/open-design) | `open-design` | Local-first OSS alternative; PATH agents (incl. Cursor); BYOK; prototype/deck exports before implementing in repo. |
| **Higgsfield** | `higgsfield` | AI **video & image** generation; motion/marketing pipelines; pair with Video Producer / compliance gates. |

### Picking a tool

- **Brand-approved comps + Claude org** → **Claude Design** first.
- **Self-hosted / OSS / CLI parity with Cursor** → **Open Design**.
- **Generated video or stills for ads, shorts, long-form** → **Higgsfield** (subject to founder spend + TOS).

### Implementation handoff

- Artifacts from any tool are **inputs**: attach exports or links to **issues / PRs**; **re-build** in target stacks (`companies/*` Next.js, Shopify Liquid, etc.).
- **Never commit** platform API keys or session tokens; follow **credentials-and-push-safety**.
